Dhlamini is a Grade 7 learner at Ngolofane Primary School. According to Lieutenant Colonel Mamphaswa Seabi, it is alleged that Dhlamini left home at 08:00 on Monday, 28 September, to go to school, but he never returned home. He was last seen wearing black jeans, a white T-shirt and white shoes. He speaks Isizulu. The police conducted the search operation in the area and the surrounding areas, as well as at his relatives and friends, but with no success. Anyone with information that can assist the police in finding the missing boy should contact the investigating officer, Sergeant Nomsa Skhosana, on 013 983 0161 or 082 303 9907. The Crime Stop number can be used by dialing 086 001 0111 or contact the nearest police station.